
@startuml

' Define the classes
class Player {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +... (other attributes)
}

class Card {
  +id: String
  +suit: Suit
  +rank: Integer
  +compareHeight(other: Card): ComparisonResult
}

enum Suit {
  DIAMONDS, HEARTS, SPADES, CLUBS
}

enum ComparisonResult {
  LOWER, EQUAL, HIGHER
}

class Deck {
  +id: String
  +cards: List<Card>
  +maxCards: Integer = 48
}

class Round {
  +id: String
  +winningPlayers: List<Player>
  +points: Integer
  +isJackRound: Boolean
  +isSoloRound: Boolean
}

class SoloRound extends Round {
  +soloType: SoloType
  +soloPlayer: Player
}

enum SoloType {
  TRUMP_SOLO, JACK_SOLO, QUEEN_SOLO
}

class ScoringTable {
  +id: String
  +rounds: List<Round>
}

' Relationships
Player "1" -- "0..*" Deck : plays
Card "1" -- "1" Deck : belongs to
Player "1" -- "0..*" Round : participates in
ScoringTable "1" -- "0..*" Round : contains
Round "1" -- "0..1" SoloRound : is a type of
SoloRound "1" -- "1" Player : has solo player

@enduml

---

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **Player**: Represents a player in the game with a unique ID.
- **Card**: Represents a playing card with suit, rank, and comparison method. It has a unique ID.
- **Suit**: An enum representing the four suits in the game.
- **ComparisonResult**: An enum for comparing card heights (lower, equal, higher).
- **Deck**: A collection of up to 48 cards with a unique ID.
- **Round**: A round in the scoring table that may have winning players and points.
- **SoloRound**: A special type of round where one player acts as the solo player. It has a type (trump, jack, queen) and a solo player.
- **ScoringTable**: Contains multiple rounds and has a unique ID.

This structure allows you to model the card game app for German clubs effectively. Let me know if you want to add more details or behavior!